A '''licence to use''' or '''LTU''' is a [[licence]] to use an [[intellectual property]] such as a [[patent]] or [[trademark]].  This is distinct from other types of licence such as a licence to manufacture or copy the invention or design.  It is the sort of licence commonly issued for the use of [[computer software]].<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7G5A2pyvCQUC&pg=PA328 |title=From patent to profit: secrets & strategies for the successful inventor |author=Bob DeMatteis}}</ref>

