{{for|a general discussion of the law of murder|murder}}
The '''Penalty Law of the People's Republic of China''',<ref>[http://www.mps.gov.cn/n16/n1282/n3493/n3763/n493954/494322.html Chinese Penalty Law (Simplified Chinese)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100731184722/http://www.mps.gov.cn/n16/n1282/n3493/n3763/n493954/494322.html |date=2010-07-31 }}</ref> as amended in 1997, provides for a penalty of death, or [[life imprisonment|imprisonment for life]] or no less than 10 years, for "killing with intent." However, the penalty for "minor killing with intent" is imprisonment for no less than 3 years. In practice, "killing with indignation" (killing someone who is obviously very harmful to the society) and killings committed in excessive [[defense (legal)|defense]] are considered "minor."
